 Interludes Live: John Legend''\n|{{yes}}\n|{{no}}\n|{{no}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Commercials===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Director\n!Writer\n!Producer\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|2015\u20132016\n|''Chapter 1'', ''Chapter 2'', ''Chapter 3''\n|{{yes}}\n|{{no}}\n|{{no}}\n| [[Apple Music]]\n|}\n\n===Music video===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Director\n!Writer\n!Producer\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[4:44 (album)#Music videos|Family Feud]]''\n|{{yes}}\n|{{yes}}\n|{{yes}}\n|Music video for [[Jay-Z]] ft. [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n|}\n\n==Awards, nominations, honors==\n*In 2012, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' featured DuVernay in its Women's Impact Report. \n* In June 2013, she was invited to both the director's and writer's branches of [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|AMPAS]].<ref name=Variety-Academy-2013>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2013/film/news/film-academy-invites-276-new-members-1200502837/|title=Film Academy Invites 276 New Members|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 28, 2013|first=Jon|last=Weisman}}</ref> DuVernay was only the second black woman, following [[Kasi Lemmons]], to be invited to the director's branch.\n* DuVernay became the inaugural recipient of the [[Tribeca Film Institute]]'s [[Heineken]] Affinity Award, receiving a $20,000 prize and industry support for future projects. DuVernay donated all the money to AFFRM, the black arthouse film collective she founded.<ref name=Indiewire-AffinityAward-2013>{{cite news|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/shadowandact/tribeca-film-institutes-inaugural-heineken-affinity-award-goes-to-ava-duvernay-20-000-industry-support|title=Tribeca Film Institute's Inaugural Heineken Affinity Award Goes To Ava DuVernay ($20,000 + Industry Support)|work=[[IndieWire]]|date=April 21, 2013|access-date=June 5, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221051946/http://blogs.indiewire.com/shadowandact/tribeca-film-institutes-inaugural-heineken-affinity-award-goes-to-ava-duvernay-20-000-industry-support|archive-date=December 21, 2014|url-status = dead}}</ref>\n* In June 2015, Duvernay was honored as part of [[Women in Film Crystal + Lucy Awards]] with the [[Dorothy Arzner]] Directors Award.<ref name=IndieWire-WiFAwards-2015>{{cite news|last=Kang|first=Inkoo|title=Nicole Kidman, Ava DuVernay, Jill Soloway Among Women in Film's 2015 Crystal + Lucy Awardees|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/womenandhollywood/nicole-kidman-ava-duvernay-jill-soloway-among-women-in-films-2015-crystal-lucy-awardees-20150331|work=[[IndieWire]]|date=March 31, 2015}}</ref>\n* In April 2015 DuVernay was chosen as one of [[Mattel]]'s \"Sheros\" of 2015. A custom-made one-of-a-kind [[Barbie]] in DuVernay's likeness was produced. The doll was auctioned off with the proceeds given to charity.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lee|first=Benjamin|title=Holding out for a Shero: Selma director Ava DuVernay gets her own Barbie doll|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/apr/24/holding-out-for-a-shero-selma-director-ava-duvernay-gets-her-own-barbie-doll|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=April 24, 2015}}</ref> Due to high demand, a collectible version of the doll was produced and sold in December of that year.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cunningham|first=Todd|title=Ava DuVernay Barbie Doll to Go on Sale Monday, Director Says|url=https://www.thewrap.com/ava-duvernay-barbie-doll-to-go-on-sale-monday-director-says/|work=[[TheWrap]]|date=December 6, 2015}}</ref>\n* In 2016, DuVernay was named to [[Oprah Winfrey|Oprah Winfrey's]] ''SuperSoul 100'' list of visionaries and influential leaders<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=August 1, 2016|title=Meet the SuperSoul100: The World's Biggest Trailblazers in One Room |url=http://www.oprah.com/spirit/supersoul100-the-worlds-biggest-trailblazers-in-one-room |work= [[O, The Oprah Magazine]]}}</ref>\n* In 2017, DuVernay became the first black woman nominated for an [[Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature]], for her film ''[[13th (film)|13th]]''.<ref>{{cite news|first=Jenelle|last=Riley|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/2017-oscars-diversity-denzel-washington-viola-davis-octavia-spencer-1201968125/|title=2017 Oscars: Diversity Makes Comeback, Record Six Black Actor Nominees|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=October 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.heraldextra.com/best-documentary-feature/article_5222cb03-b20d-5fa7-923b-3ae5950221d2.html|title=Best Documentary Feature|work=[[Daily Herald (Utah)|Daily Herald]]|date=January 18, 2017}}</ref>\n*In 2017, DuVernay was the recipient of Smithsonian Magazine's American Ingenuity Award for Visual Arts.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/ingenuity/ceremonies/2017-winners/|title=2017 American Ingenuity Award Winners|work=Smithsonian|access-date=2018-10-15}}</ref>\n*In 2018, DuVernay won Entertainer of the Year at the [[49th NAACP Image Awards]] for her work in 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-naacp-image-award-winners-complete-list-1064208|title=NAACP Image Awards: Full List of Winners|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 14, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]] declared DuVernay and actor [[Benedict Cumberbatch]] to be the Most Beautiful Vegan Celebs of 2018.<ref name=ETCanada-PETA-BeautifulVegan-2018>{{cite news|last1=Furdyk|first1=Brent|title=Benedict Cumberbatch, Ava DuVernay Named PETA's 'Most Beautiful Vegan Celebs' Of 2018|url=https://etcanada.com/news/346447/benedict-cumberbatch-ava-duvernay-named-petas-most-beautiful-vegan-celebs-of-2018/|work=[[Entertainment Tonight Canada|ET Canada]]|date=11 July 2018}}</ref>\n \n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n|-\n|2011\n|[[African-American Film Critics Association|African-American Film Critics]]\n|Best Screenplay\n|rowspan=4|''I Will Follow''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=12|2012\n|rowspan=2|[[Black Reel Awards]]\n|[[Black Reel Award for Best S