gis]] in January 2016, asking whether \"blacks and other minorities have fully realized lives rather than serve as scenery in white stories.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Dargis|first=Manohla|title=Sundance Fights Tide With Films Like 'The Birth of a Nation'|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/30/movies/sundance-fights-tide-with-films-like-the-birth-of-a-nation.html|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=January 29, 2016}}</ref> It aims to point out the lack of people of color in [[Hollywood]] [[movie]]s, through a measure of their importance to a particular movie or the lack of a gratuitous link to white actors.<ref name=2016-02-01_TC>{{cite news|url=https://www.thecut.com/2016/02/could-this-be-the-bechdel-test-for-race.html|title=Could This Be the Bechdel Test for Race|last=Evans|first=Dayna|date=February 1, 2016|work=The Cut|publisher=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|nowrap=yes}}\n* {{Official website|www.avaduvernay.com}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n* {{IMDb name|1148550}}\n* [http://www.makers.com/ava-duvernay Ava DuVernay] at ''[[Makers: Women Who Make America]]''\n\n{{Ava DuVernay}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Ava DuVernay\n|list =\n{{BAFTA Los Angeles Britannia Awards}}\n{{Black Reel Award for Outstanding Director}}\n{{Black Reel Award for Outstanding Screenplay, Adapted or Original}}\n{{EmmyAward NonfictionProgrammingWriting}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:DuVernay, Ava}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:African-American film directors]]\n[[Category:African-American film producers]]\n[[Category:African-American screenwriters]]\n[[Category:African-American television directors]]\n[[Category:African-American television producers]]\n[[Category:American film producers]]\n[[Category:American people of Creole descent]]\n[[Category:American people of French descent]]\n[[Category:American publicists]]\n[[Category:American television directors]]\n[[Category:American women film directors]]\n[[Category:American women film producers]]\n[[Category:American women screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Film directors from California]]\n[[Category:Film producers from California]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Louisiana Creole people]]\n[[Category:People from Lynwood, California]]\n[[Category:Primetime Emmy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from California]]\n[[Category:Television producers from California]]\n[[Category:University of California, Los Angeles alumni]]\n[[Category:Women television directors]]\n[[Category:Women television producers]]\n[[Category:Women television writers]]\n[[Category:Writers from Long Beach, California]]\n", "name_user": "Naraht", "label": "safe", "comment": "linkAlpha Kappa AlphausingFind link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ava_DuVernay"}
